# Local Gradle build settings — copy to local.properties and fill in your values.
# This file is committed to version control as a template.
# local.properties is git-ignored and must NOT be committed.
#
# First-time setup:
#
#   cp local.properties.example local.properties
#   # Edit local.properties and fill in SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
#   # (the only two required keys for backend connectivity). Other settings
#   # are optional — leave them empty for local-only mode (no analytics, no
#   # subscription, no live backend).
#
# Read by:
#   - shared/build.gradle.kts          → SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY,
#                                          REVENUECAT_API_KEY_ANDROID
#   - androidApp/build.gradle.kts      → SENTRY_DSN_ANDROID, POSTHOG_API_KEY,
#                                          POSTHOG_HOST, KEYSTORE_PASSWORD,
#                                          KEY_ALIAS, KEY_PASSWORD
#
# These keys are shared with iosApp/local.xcconfig where applicable (Supabase
# URL + Publishable Key are the same on both platforms; Sentry and PostHog
# have iOS-specific equivalents — see iosApp/local.xcconfig.example).
#
# CI fallback: each key is also read from the matching shell environment
# variable when local.properties is absent. CI workflows inject these via
# GitHub Environment Secrets — see docs/en/ops/release-secrets.md for the
# server-side rotation matrix.

# === Required: backend connectivity =========================================
# Empty values cause the app to start in local-only mode — sign-in, profile,
# Discovery feed, and every backend-dependent screen will fail. Setting these
# is the only step needed to unblock account creation + basic app usage.

# Supabase project URL — from Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API.
SUPABASE_URL=

# Supabase Publishable key (`sb_publishable_…` form, post-2025-11-01). Safe
# to embed in client binaries (RLS enforced server-side). The legacy `anon`
# JWT key was deprecated 2025-11-01 — do not use it for new builds.
SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# === Optional: analytics + crash reporting ===================================
# Empty values disable each SDK. Even with keys configured, init is also
# gated on the user's analytics opt-in toggle in Settings (Phase 39.2).

# Sentry DSN for the Android Sentry project. Get this from:
#   Sentry > Settings > Projects > skeinly-android > Client Keys (DSN).
SENTRY_DSN_ANDROID=

# PostHog Project API Key (phc_… prefix). Get from:
#   PostHog > Settings > Project > Project API Key.
POSTHOG_API_KEY=

# PostHog host. Default is the public US cloud. Override only if you self-
# host PostHog or use the EU region (https://eu.i.posthog.com).
POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.i.posthog.com

# === Optional: F1 Pro subscription (Phase 41) ================================
# RevenueCat Public Android SDK Key — Dashboard > API Keys > Public Android
# SDK Key (starts with `goog_`). See vendor-setup.md A0d-1 + release-secrets
# §20. Empty key ⇒ RevenueCatConfig.isConfigured = false ⇒ paywall surfaces
# a "subscriptions unavailable in this build" message rather than crashing.
REVENUECAT_API_KEY_ANDROID=

# === Optional: Android Release signing =======================================
# Required ONLY for `make release-aab-local` / Play Store uploads. Debug
# builds (`./gradlew :androidApp:installDebug` / `make android-install`) do
# not need signing — they sign with the default Android debug keystore.
#
# Setup: generate or import a signing keystore via Android Studio
#   (Build > Generate Signed Bundle / APK > new keystore) or via keytool,
#   save it as `keystore.jks` at the REPOSITORY ROOT (also git-ignored),
#   then fill in the three values below.
#
# CI release builds receive these via GitHub Secrets (KEYSTORE_FILE_BASE64
# + KEYSTORE_PASSWORD + KEY_ALIAS + KEY_PASSWORD) per release-secrets.md.

# KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=
# KEY_ALIAS=
# KEY_PASSWORD=
